### Telemetry API – full flow demo
### Use with VS Code REST Client or similar. Set BASE to your API root (e.g. http://localhost:5244).
@BASE = http://localhost:5244
@CORRELATION_ID = demo-{{$guid}}

### 1. Create instrument
POST {{BASE}}/instruments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "LC-1",
  "type": "Chromatograph",
  "serialNumber": "SN-001"
}

### 2. Create run (replace INSTRUMENT_ID with id from step 1)
@INSTRUMENT_ID = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
POST {{BASE}}/runs
Content-Type: application/json
X-Correlation-Id: {{CORRELATION_ID}}

{
  "instrumentId": "{{INSTRUMENT_ID}}",
  "sampleId": "S-001",
  "methodName": "MethodA",
  "methodVersion": "1.0"
}

### 3. Queue run (replace RUN_ID with id from step 2)
@RUN_ID = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
POST {{BASE}}/runs/{{RUN_ID}}/queue?actor=operator

### 4. Start run
POST {{BASE}}/runs/{{RUN_ID}}/start?actor=operator

### 5. Get run
GET {{BASE}}/runs/{{RUN_ID}}

### 6. Get timeline
GET {{BASE}}/runs/{{RUN_ID}}/timeline

### 7a. Complete run (terminal)
POST {{BASE}}/runs/{{RUN_ID}}/complete?actor=operator

### 7b. Or fail run (terminal)
# POST {{BASE}}/runs/{{RUN_ID}}/fail?actor=operator

### 7c. Or cancel run (terminal from Created/Queued/Running)
# POST {{BASE}}/runs/{{RUN_ID}}/cancel?actor=operator

### 8. Download support bundle
POST {{BASE}}/runs/{{RUN_ID}}/support-bundle?lastLogEntries=100

### --- Error case: start without queue (expect 409) ---
# Create another run, then call start without queue:
# POST {{BASE}}/runs/{{RUN_ID}}/start
